{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras","doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift","doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/Collection"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/Collection\/subscript(safe:)"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:Sl11SwiftExtrasE4safe7ElementQzSg5IndexQz_tcip","roleHeading":"Instance Subscript","modules":[{"name":"SwiftExtras","relatedModules":["Swift"]}],"title":"subscript(safe:)","symbolKind":"subscript","conformance":{"constraints":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Self"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Collection"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"conformancePrefix":[{"text":"Conforms when","type":"text"}],"availabilityPrefix":[{"text":"Available when","type":"text"}]},"extendedModule":"Swift","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"subscript"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"safe"},{"kind":"text","text":" _: "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sl5IndexQa","text":"Index"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ST7ElementQa","text":"Element"},{"kind":"text","text":"?"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"subscript"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"safe"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"index"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sl5IndexQa","text":"Index"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ST7ElementQa","text":"Element"},{"kind":"text","text":"? { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"index","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The position of the element to access."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the index is within the bounds of the collection, "},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"the element at that position is returned. Otherwise, "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"return-value","text":"Return Value","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The element at the specified index if it is within the collection’s bounds; otherwise, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This subscript provides a safe way to access elements within the collection by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returning "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instead of crashing when accessing an index out of bounds."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is useful for avoiding runtime errors when the exact count of the collection"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"might not be known or when dealing with dynamic data sources."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This approach ensures that attempts to access indices outside the valid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"range simply result in "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", allowing for more graceful handling of such cases."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example usage:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]","if let number = numbers[safe: 3] {","    print(number) \/\/ Prints \"4\"","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\")","}","","if let outOfBoundsNumber = numbers[safe: 10] {","    print(outOfBoundsNumber)","} else {","    print(\"Index out of bounds\") \/\/ Prints \"Index out of bounds\"","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method enhances the safety and readability of collection access, "},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"especially in more complex logic where bounds checks are necessary."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift\/collection\/subscript(safe:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Accesses the element at the specified position in a safe manner.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://SwiftExtras/documentation/SwiftExtras/Swift/Collection":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift\/Collection","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"extension"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sl","text":"Collection"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Collection"}],"title":"Collection","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift\/collection","abstract":[]},"doc://SwiftExtras/documentation/SwiftExtras/Swift":{"title":"Swift","url":"\/documentation\/swiftextras\/swift","role":"collection","type":"topic","abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftExtras\/documentation\/SwiftExtras\/Swift"},"doc://SwiftExtras/documentation/SwiftExtras/Swift/Collection/subscript(safe:)":{"title":"subscript(safe:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"subscript"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"safe"},{"kind":"text","text":" _: "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeI